{
  "id": "infiniflow_ragflow_14666",
  "repo_name": "infiniflow/ragflow",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow",
  "base_commit": "d51fb88573861e68f40d795be93101f25567b8dd",
  "pr_number": 14666,
  "issue_number": 14651,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Agent-with-tools citation generation crashes when retrieved chunk has document_metadata: null",
  "issue_body": "# [Bug]: Agent-with-tools citation generation crashes when retrieved chunk has `document_metadata: null`\n\n## Description\n\nThe base Docs QA / Agent template successfully retrieves a dataset document, but then crashes during citation/reference generation.\n\nThe retrieval itself works. The failure occurs after the retrieval tool returns a valid result and after the model completes a text response. The crash appears to be caused by a retrieved chunk containing `document_metadata: null`, which is not handled safely in `kb_prompt()`.\n\n---\n\n## Self Checks\n\n* [x] I have searched for existing issues, including closed ones.\n* [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report.\n* [x] I have not modified the RAGFlow issue template structure.\n\n---\n\n## RAGFlow workspace code commit ID\n\n`v0.25.1-75-g59c35100c`\n\nThe running container logs report:\n\n```text\nRAGFlow version: v0.25.1-75-g59c35100c\n```\n\n---\n\n## RAGFlow image version\n\n```text\ninfiniflow/ragflow:nightly\n```\n\nContainer:\n\n```text\ndocker-ragflow-cpu-1\n```\n\n---\n\n## Other environment information\n\nDeployment:\n\n```text\nDocker Compose\n```\n\nRelevant environment:\n\n```text\nDOC_ENGINE=elasticsearch\nElasticsearch 8.11.3\nMySQL 8.0.39\nMinIO RELEASE.2025-06-13T11-33-47Z\nValkey 8\nRAGFLOW_IMAGE=infiniflow/ragflow:nightly\n```\n\nModel / provider:\n\n```text\nLLM provider: DeepSeek via LiteLLM\nModel: deepseek-chat\n```\n\nAgent setup:\n\n```text\nBase Docs QA / Agent template\nDataset retrieval tool attached to the agent\nTool name in logs: search_my_dateset_0\n```\n\n---\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nThe agent successfully retrieves a relevant document from the dataset, but then fails during citation/reference generation with:\n\n```text\nAttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'items'\n```\n\nExample retrieval immediately before crash:\n\n```text\n[ToolCall] invoke name=search_my_dateset_0 arguments={'query': '<dataset query>'}\n\n[ToolCall] done name=search_my_dateset_0 elapsed=2.96s result=\nID: 153\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Title: <retrieved document title>.pdf\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Content:\n<retrieved document content begins here>\n```\n\nThe model then completes a text response:\n\n```text\n[ToolLoop] round=1 completed with text response, exiting\n```\n\nThen RAGFlow crashes in the citation generation path:\n\n```text\nERROR 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'items'\n\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/ragflow/api/apps/restful_apis/agent_api.py\", line 990, in sse\n    async for ans in canvas.run(query=query, files=files, user_id=user_id, inputs=inputs):\n  File \"/ragflow/agent/canvas.py\", line 551, in run\n    async for m in stream:\n  File \"/ragflow/agent/component/message.py\", line 219, in _stream\n    async for t in iter_obj:\n  File \"/ragflow/agent/component/agent_with_tools.py\", line 302, in stream_output_with_tools_async\n    async for delta in self._gen_citations_async(answer):\n  File \"/ragflow/agent/component/agent_with_tools.py\", line 317, in _gen_citations_async\n    formated_refer = kb_prompt(retrievals, self.chat_mdl.max_length, True)\n                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/ragflow/rag/prompts/generator.py\", line 133, in kb_prompt\n    for k, v in meta.items():\n                ^^^^^^^^^^\nAttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'items'\n```\n\n---\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nThe base Docs QA / Agent template should not crash when a retrieved chunk has missing or null document metadata.\n\nExpected behavior would be one of:\n\n1. Treat `document_metadata: null` as an empty dictionary.\n2. Skip metadata rendering for that chunk.\n3. Continue generating the response and references without raising an exception.\n\nThe agent should return a normal answer because retrieval succeeded and the retrieved content was valid.\n\n---\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run RAGFlow using Docker Compose with the nightly image:\n\n```text\nRAGFLOW_IMAGE=infiniflow/ragflow:nightly\nDOC_ENGINE=elasticsearch\n```\n\n2. Confirm the running version:\n\n```text\nRAGFlow version: v0.25.1-75-g59c35100c\n```\n\n3. Use the base Docs QA / Agent template with a dataset retrieval tool attached to the agent.\n\n4. Query the agent using any dataset query that retrieves a chunk whose `document_metadata` field exists but is `null`.\n\n5. Observe that the dataset retrieval tool successfully returns a relevant document.\n\n6. Observe that the agent completes a text response.\n\n7. Observe the backend crash during `_gen_citations_async()` / `kb_prompt()` with:\n\n```text\nAttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'items'\n```\n\n---\n\n## Root cause analysis\n\nThe failing source code is in:\n\n```text\n/ragflow/rag/prompts/generator.py\n```\n\nCurrent code:\n\n```python\nmeta = ck.get(\"document_metadata\", {})\nfor k, v in meta.items():\n    cnt += draw_node(k, v)\n```\n\nThis is unsafe if the chunk contains:\n\n```python\n\"document_metadata\": None\n```\n\nIn Python, `dict.get(\"document_metadata\", {})` only returns the default `{}` if the key is missing. If the key exists and its value is `None`, the result is `None`. The following call then crashes:\n\n```python\nmeta.items()\n```\n\nThe call path is:\n\n```text\n/ragflow/agent/component/agent_with_tools.py\n\u2192 stream_output_with_tools_async()\n\u2192 _gen_citations_async(answer)\n\u2192 kb_prompt(retrievals, self.chat_mdl.max_length, True)\n\u2192 /ragflow/rag/prompts/generator.py\n\u2192 meta.items()\n```\n\nRelevant source inspection showed:\n\n```python\nasync def _gen_citations_async(self, text):\n    retrievals = self._canvas.get_reference()\n    retrievals = {\"chunks\": list(retrievals[\"chunks\"].values()), \"doc_aggs\": list(retrievals[\"doc_aggs\"].values())}\n    formated_refer = kb_prompt(retrievals, self.chat_mdl.max_length, True)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Local workaround tested\n\nChanging this:\n\n```python\nmeta = ck.get(\"document_metadata\", {})\nfor k, v in meta.items():\n```\n\nto this:\n\n```python\nmeta = ck.get(\"document_metadata\") or {}\nfor k, v in meta.items():\n```\n\nresolved the crash locally.\n\nAfter this change, the same agent and dataset retrieval path returned a normal answer with document IDs/citations instead of crashing.\n\n---\n\n## Suggested fix\n\nMake metadata handling null-safe in `kb_prompt()`.\n\nRecommended change:\n\n```python\nmeta = ck.get(\"document_metadata\") or {}\n```\n\nAlternative defensive change:\n\n```python\nfor k, v in (meta or {}).items():\n```\n\nThis would prevent the citation/reference formatter from crashing when a retrieved chunk has `document_metadata: null`.\n\n---\n\n## Additional information\n\nThe UI Cite toggle appeared to be disabled, but the backend still entered:\n\n```text\n_gen_citations_async()\n```\n\nThis may indicate that either:\n\n1. the Cite toggle is not respected in this Agent-with-tools path, or\n2. this path always performs reference formatting regardless of the UI setting.\n\nThe important point is that retrieval succeeds and the failure occurs only in post-retrieval citation/reference formatting.\n\n---\n\n## Why this matters\n\nThis affects the base Docs QA / Agent template. A single retrieved chunk with `document_metadata: null` can cause the entire agent response to fail, even though retrieval and model generation both succeed.\n\nThe bug is small but high-impact because the base template should be robust against null metadata in retrieved chunks.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-08T08:54:33.000Z",
